      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING NANGAR (8) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish a nose away in second (29.65) at this track in a Grade 5/6 over 520m. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Can go on with it. MASQUERADE PARTY (2) had to overcome a collision in the run but could manage only a distant third (29.94) in a Grade 5/6 over 520m at this track. Harder here but expected to feature again. CYNTHIA KEEPING (1) hit the ground running from out wide and was on speed early but swamped late when 6th at Mandurah in a Grade 5. Must be included in calculations. JUST A BINDI (5) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
